mozci.py
- Do explicit imports
- Don't pass AUTH to other modules (they now calculate it themselves)
- Ask buildapi to tell us if the revision is a valid one to trigger jobs against
- Do not add files to payload if there are no files
- Fix returning list of requests for a trigger() call

buildapi.py
- Do explicit imports
- Determine AUTH rather than expect it to be passed
- valid_revision() checks that we can request jobs for it
- raise an exception if we're trying to request a job for an invalid revision
- add query_repo_url()

pushlog.py
- Do explicit imports
- Determine AUTH rather than expect it to be passed
- Determine repo_url based on repo_name
- Rename query_changeset() to query_revision_info()
- Allow requesting full information for changesets

misc.py
- Do explicit imports
- Determine AUTH rather than expect it to be passed

trigger.py
- Fix issues with multiple requests
